    <title>Foreclosure Relief and Extension for Servicemembers Act of 2015</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2015-04-30T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2015-04-30</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-05-22T16:43:12Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Foreclosure Relief and Extension for Servicemembers Act of 2015</b></p> <p> Amends the Honoring America's Veterans and Caring for Camp Lejeune Families Act of 2012 to make permanent the extended one-year period after a servicemember's military service during which: (1) a court may stay proceedings to enforce an obligation on real or personal property owned by the servicemember prior to such military service; and (2) the sale, foreclosure, or seizure of such property is invalid without a court order or agreement. (Currently, the extended one-year period is scheduled to expire on December 31, 2014, and return to a nine-month period under the Servicemembers Civil Relief Act.)</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
